  <prompt>Follow `jps-playbook-design` skill. Author repo JSON source-of-truth file at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json` defining the `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` playbook: header fields (`sprk_playbookcode = "BRIEF-NARRATE"`, `sprk_playbooktype = 0` AiAnalysis NOT 2 Notification, `sprk_playbookmode = 1` NodeBased, `sprk_triggertype = 0` Manual, `sprk_capabilities = 100000006` Summarize) plus `sprk_configjson` node graph: Start &#x2192; LoadKnowledge (channel registry) &#x2192; [GenerateTldr &#x2016; GenerateChannelNarratives (parallel per channel — ADR-037)] &#x2192; ValidateEntityNames (Tool ActionType 141) &#x2192; ReturnResponse. Validate via `jps-validate` skill before completion. Include Component Justification block (CLAUDE.md §11): existing=none for narrate-grounded use case, extension=No, cost-of-doing-nothing=`/narrate` cannot dispatch to JPS without this playbook (FR-12 binding).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook designer with expertise in node-based graph composition (ADR-037 multinode output composition), Skill nodes (AI), Tool nodes (post-LLM validation), and parallel-branch fan-out semantics.</role>

  <goal>A valid, jps-validate-passing JSON file at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json` defining the BRIEF-NARRATE playbook header + node graph. The graph references the 3 Action codes deployed in PR 1 (BRIEF-NARRATE-TLDR, BRIEF-NARRATE-CHANNEL, BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES). Parallel fan-out for channel narratives modeled per ADR-037. Component justification block present.</goal>

